    {
      "id": "PopularPost57913",
      "post_content": "@ Holgir: No, you cannot field wipe with this card. Since the card itself is dealing the damage and the first damage resolving off the stack will kill it, the next however many abilities you have sac'd artifacts for will fizzle off the stack since he can't do damage from the graveyard.  \n  \nHowever, if you were to use a [Mark of Asylum](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mark of Asylum) in combination with this card, you can effectively field wipe, but it's going to be far easier to use the common combo with [Chain Reaction](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Chain Reaction). But this could end up being cheaper and better themed to a goblin artifact deck if that's what you're going for, in which case I would suggest [Sword of the Meek](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sword of the Meek). However, good players will tell you this combo is much better fit to other decks... cough broken thopters cough...  \n  \n---Edit::: [Furnace of Rath](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Furnace of Rath) = lols in multplayer...",
      "posted_by": "OpenSeasonNoobs",
      "html": "<div class=\"post evenItem\" id=\"PopularPost57913\" style=\"background-color: rgba(255,255,255,0.08);\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_post\">@ Holgir: No, you cannot field wipe with this card. Since the card itself is dealing the damage and the first damage resolving off the stack will kill it, the next however many abilities you have sac'd artifacts for will fizzle off the stack since he can't do damage from the graveyard.<br/><br/>However, if you were to use a <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Mark of Asylum\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Mark of Asylum\">Mark of Asylum</a> in combination with this card, you can effectively field wipe, but it's going to be far easier to use the common combo with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Chain Reaction\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Chain Reaction\">Chain Reaction</a>. But this could end up being cheaper and better themed to a goblin artifact deck if that's what you're going for, in which case I would suggest <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Sword of the Meek\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Sword of the Meek\">Sword of the Meek</a>. However, good players will tell you this combo is much better fit to other decks... cough broken thopters cough...<br/><br/>---Edit::: <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Furnace of Rath\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Furnace of Rath\">Furnace of Rath</a> = lols in multplayer...</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"../../Classes/Controls/#\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl02_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '57913'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n 